This README contains instructions for running the version of pokete
we have been working on over the last few weeks. It is important that
you do not follow the install instructions in the original README, as
our changes have not all been pushed upstream.

Python3.12 and pip24.2 or newer are required.

To install pokete with the changes we have made, in a terminal, do the following :
    - Clone this repo into your desired directory:
        'git clone https://github.com/squidaboni/COMP490_Final.git'
    - Navigate into the project folder: cd ~/.../COMP490_Final
    - Run the command: 'pip install -e .'
    - To confirm you have installed the forked version, run the command 'pip show pokete'.
      The field "Editable project location:" should match your working directory.
    - To play the game, run the command 'python -m pokete' (or 'python3 -m pokete')
